I cannot rave enough about Mixteco! Every time I’m in Chicago we eat here and it has never disappointed. The best burritos, tacos, quesadillas and horchata!
I eat here like once a week, the tacos are amazing, the guac is so good and it’s such a fast deli every/pick up time!

Cant say enough good things about mixteco. The value is great - I usually order a fiesta bowl and am able to make 2 meals out of it. The people are quick and friendly, orders are usually ready in less than 7 minutes even during peak hours. Best of all the food is fresh and high quality. Salsas made in house, fresh veggies, beans and rice. If you are in a dinner rut, order from mixteco! And Get the churros if you're feeling a little crazy.

I recently stopped by the other day. First and foremost I was happy to see the staff were following Covid guidelines and all staff were wearing mask. The customer service was above and beyond. They’re currently offering pickup/takeout and delivery. Where do I start with food? They have such a nice selection from tacos, burritos, salads, quesadillas and desserts. I love the variety of meat options they have. The chicken quesadillas were my favorite! Wow I’m still craving those! I live in LA and we have some of the best Mexican food around but I woke up today thinking about these quesadillas honestly the best I’ve ever had lol. My nephew loved the steak tacos they’re perfect for about 2-3 people. The shrimp taco dinner plate was so delicious and comes with rice and beans. The chimichangas wow yeah I need to another visit soon the rice, beans and cheese were so bomb and I loved the Crispiness okay yeah I’m getting hungry again  I definitely recommend checking them out! P.S I know paper money isn’t good right now due to Covid but please put a tip jar out for the staff
always good always delicious...fast service...super fast delivery.

Went to Mixteco for the first time last night. Staff was friendly, food came quick, no hassle - just the experience you want during COVID.  I ordered the chicken enchilada plate. Three enchiladas, refried beans and rice. I feel like it was a good value, I have leftovers for another meal, event! The chicken was moist, not soggy. The sauce had the right amount of heat for a mild dish.  Will come back soon.
Absolutely delicious food and SUPER quick!! Love this place.
My boyfriend and I got the enchilado suizo and it was delicious!!! Highly recommend. Can’t wait to go back to try the tacos!

Efficient service and delicious food!! I would recommend Mixteco to anyone looking for an excellent and filling (and quick!) meal. The quality is great for the price, and I will be back in the future.
Best Mexican food in Chicago. The delivery and customer service was amazing. Can’t wait to try other things on the menu.

I got the taco salad to go and used the entire salsa as my dressing. This salsa verde was SO GOOD. It was so flavorful and was the star of the dish for me. The salad was fresh, creamy from sour cream, guac, and crunchy. Excellent price point and lots of protein options. I went with chicken for a lighter option. Highly recommend.

Mixteco is a fun new spot on Belmont I have been wanting to try! I got the Fiesta Bowl with carne asada and it was so good - would absolutely recommend. I personally liked this bowl better than a bowl at chipotle. There was a better balance of the ingredients and better flavor. Next time, I might get the tacos - that's what my roommate ordered and they looked really good! Also, Antonio was super nice and helpful (I changed my mind a few times....ooops - thank you Antonio!!)  Overall, great! We did carry out and the restaurant was super clean too. Will definitely be back.

I had Mixteco for the first time today and it was amazing! There are so many options. I had "the works" burrito with steak. It was one of the best burritos I have ever had! My friend got the fajita quesadilla and she said it was very good. We also split guac. Everything was so fresh! Everyone needs to try this place!

The chicken in the burrito bowl was so tender. The chicken melted in my mouth. I ordered the Azteca De Oro with the pulled chicken paired with guacamole. I cannot rave about this enough! A 5-star experience all around. The staff was friendly and the food was prepared to perfection. If you are looking for Mexican food in Lakeview, this is the go-to spot.

Mixteco is such an awesome neighborhood spot in Lakeview. Their tacos are delicious - my favorites are the carne asada tacos - while the churros are to die for. Also loved the horchata. Definitely recommend a visit!

My go to Mexican place in the city! Staff is always friendly including delivery drivers! I was recently inside the restaurant and saw superb social distancing and sanitation practices. Delicious, and a great business!

OK, so this was the BEST visit ever. Talk about COVID-friendly. Mixteco's food is amazing and this was my first time trying it. If you are looking for delicious Mexican food, look no further. I tried the Tacos Alambre Combo, see photos attached. I ordered the dinner portion which was the perfect amount. So filling. This is a must-try location! Can't make it in the restaurant? Ordering directly from the website and save 15% on your entire order. I will be back, Mixteco! Thank you for the wonderful service and fantastic meal. 5 stars across the board.
Mexican food and the setting here is above par. I give this place double thumbs up. I will be back with my relatives.

We ordered from Mixteco tonight for the first time and it was AMAZING! Delivery was so fast too. We got the chicken chimichanga, fire grilled quesadilla and churros! They were all soo yummy! We will definitely be ordering again soon!! Highly recommend!!

SO GOOD - my go-to tex-mex in Lakeview! Fast and friendly service with all the necessary safety precautions in place, making my visit easy and stress free. My meal was ready in under ten minutes; you can definitely tell they use fresh/top quality ingredients.

I love their sauces and vegetarian options. They have super tasty vegetarian enchiladas with fajita style veggies and flavorful grilled tofu. They also have wonderful guacamole, salsa, and horchata! I highly recommend this spot, they were very quick too.

Some of the best tacos in the city! Actually, some of the best Mexican food overall! Go-to's include ALL the tacos (especially steak and chicken), chicken enchiladas, burritos, taquitos, quesadillas and their new queso dip! Everything is always fresh, hot and delicious! Tastes authentic and great quality! Service is awesome! If you pick up you will notice the restaurant is sparkling clean with friendly staff! And if you order delivery it's super fast! Highly recommend if you haven't already tried!

I absolutely loved trying out Mixteco! I had the Enchilado Suizo Burrito and I would go as far as to say it was the best burrito I’ve ever had! The flavor was amazing and I would be remissed if I didn’t mention the grilled tofu as a protein option. It tasted incredible and was soooo flavorful... I would order it on its own! I can’t wait to be back to Mixteco to try other items on the menu!
Delicious! Had amazing Baja grilled fish tacos and the steak quesadilla. Highly recommend.

There are a number of places to go for good Mexican or Tex-Mex food in Lakeview, and Mixteco Mexican Grill is definitely one of them.  First, I really like the location.  It’s located conveniently on Belmont St. in the heart of Lakeview.  It’s right in between the red line/brown line stop and Clark Street.  Second, the food is very good.  I tried the works burrito with steak, chicken nachos and tres Leches Cake for dessert.  The works burrito lives up to its name as it is stuffed with ingredients.  They also did not skimp on the steak.  Next, the chicken nachos where very good.  The chicken was tender and the crispy chips were loaded with beans, cheese and guacamole.  I liked that the chips were strong enough to hold all of the ingredients.  While I enjoyed the nachos and the burrito, the true highlight of the meal was the tres leches cake I had for dessert.  It was creamy, moist and was sitting in a pool of condensed milk.  No meal is complete here without it.  Third, the staff was friendly and the service was super fast.  If you are in Lakeview, skip the Chipotle and come here.

The TV was so loud he couldn’t hear us but when I told him I couldn’t hear him he just rolled his eyes at me. If you can’t hear your customers then you should turn the tv volume down. We didn’t order anything complicated so it’s shocking he didn’t get either order correct even after we corrected him multiple times.
